Add fchmodat2 (syscall 452, Linux 6.6+) support to proot.

GNU coreutils `cp` on a 6.6+ kernel sets directory permissions via
fchmodat2(dirfd, path, mode, AT_SYMLINK_NOFOLLOW) — the only chmod variant
supporting AT_SYMLINK_NOFOLLOW. proot ab2e3464 (2026-02-20) has no knowledge of
this syscall, so in seccomp mode it is never trapped, the guest path is never
translated, and the kernel returns ENOENT ("cp: setting permissions for
'source': No such file or directory"). This breaks any build that cp -r's a
read-only directory tree (e.g. cargo vendor staging) under nix-on-droid.

Wire fchmodat2 exactly like the existing faccessat2: enum (sysnums.list), arch
number tables (452 on arm64/x86_64/arm/i386), the AT_SYMLINK_NOFOLLOW-aware
translation group in enter.c (flags in SYSARG_4), and the seccomp filter list.

See docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-23-proot-fchmodat2-design.md

diff -ruN p2-orig/src/syscall/enter.c p2-work/src/syscall/enter.c
--- a/src/syscall/enter.c	2026-06-24 00:03:57.657185380 +0400
+++ b/src/syscall/enter.c	2026-06-24 00:04:08.281260029 +0400
@@ -408,6 +408,7 @@
 			status = translate_sysarg(tracee, SYSARG_1, REGULAR);
 		break;
 
+	case PR_fchmodat2:
 	case PR_fchownat:
 	case PR_fstatat64:
 	case PR_newfstatat:
